I live upstate NY and before leaving my house I called and placed my order and explained I am coming from far. I started my drive and half way through I told them I am about 30-45 minuites away please make sure to have my three plates prepared. She said ok "come, come". I got there and they had no more casava leaf. I was so upset. I said I CALLED AND LET YOU PEOPLE KNOW, NOT ONCE BUT TWICE!!!! Every time I am in the Bronx ,I come here. The amount of food you get for your money is great. The food is usually delicious. This time the food was horrible.The dibi was DRY , very DRY! Even the onion sauce tasted off. I am so disappointed. I will not be returning back here ever again.
